CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper February 22, 1947, pg. 22, reads: "Plan Benefit for Orphans - Alpha Kappa Alpha sorors will sponsor a benefit event for the Davis Home for Colored Children on the evening of March 1 at the Home on Simonton Street. Left to right are: Jacqueline Ford, Pearl Johnson, Helen Lee, chairman of the panning committee; Marian Anderson, Olivia King, president, and Lila Terry. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Alpha Kappa Alpha sorority members Jacqueline Ford, Pearl Johnson, Helen Lee, Marian Anderson, Olivia King, and Lila Terry holding books and gathered in interior with pillar
